==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Anticoherer
<hw>An`ti*co*her"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Wireless
Teleg.)</fld> <def>A device, one form of which consists of a scratched
deposit of silver on glass, used in connection with the receiving
apparatus for reading wireless signals. The electric waves falling on
this contrivance increase its resistance several times. The anticoherer
can be used in conjunction with a telephone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Anticonstitutional</ent>⟦br⟧
